                  </hi>. I am the wife of Page Flowers, an engine-driver, of 7, Walnut-tree-walk, Lambeth. The prisoner's brother lives in the kitchen—I have seen the prisoner two or three times—on 21st Jan. I went out at</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185002040082"></xptr>
               <p>ten o'clock at night, and was not home till twelve—next morning I missed this sugar-basin—it is my husband's, and worth 25<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. as old silver—my par<lb></lb>lour-door was not locked—a person must pass it to go to the kitchen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> On the Monday evening, I left my brother's to go home; as I came out, I found this, and thought it was a bit of tin.</p>
